# Copy to .env and adjust as needed.
#
# ── Database ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Prisma uses two URLs:
#   DATABASE_URL → pooled connection used by the running app
#   DIRECT_URL   → direct connection used by `prisma migrate` / introspection
# Locally these can be identical. On Supabase they MUST differ (pooler vs 5432).

# --- Local Postgres (docker-compose) -----------------------------------------
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://automate:automate@localhost:5432/automate?schema=public"
DIRECT_URL="postgresql://automate:automate@localhost:5432/automate?schema=public"

# --- Supabase (standalone test project, then later the dealer-portal project) -
# All consumer tables live in a dedicated `automate` schema so they never touch
# the dealer portal's own tables. Copy these from:
#   Supabase Dashboard → "Connect" (top bar) → ORMs / Prisma, or
#   Project Settings → Database → Connection string
#
# You can paste Supabase's bare "Connect" URLs as-is — if a URL has no
# `?schema=…`, the app defaults it to `automate` (src/prismaAdapter.ts +
# prisma.config.ts). Add `?schema=public` (or another) only to override that.
#
# NOTE: the *direct* host (db.<ref>.supabase.co) is IPv6-only on the free tier,
# so use the POOLER (pooler.supabase.com, IPv4) for BOTH urls:
#
# DATABASE_URL = Transaction pooler (port 6543) — for the running app:
# DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres.<project-ref>:<db-password>@aws-0-<region>.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres?schema=automate&pgbouncer=true&connection_limit=1"
#
# DIRECT_URL = Session pooler (port 5432 on the pooler host) — for migrations:
# DIRECT_URL="postgresql://postgres.<project-ref>:<db-password>@aws-0-<region>.pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres?schema=automate"

# ── Auth / server ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
AUTH_SECRET="change-me-in-production"
PORT=4000
# Where the local StorageProvider writes files (relative to server/)
UPLOAD_DIR=uploads
# Public origin used in upload URLs returned to the app
PUBLIC_ORIGIN=http://localhost:4000
